rview Module that generates technical questions dynamically based on structured JD and resume data\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Implement a Response Scorer that evaluates candidate answers against JD and resume criteria\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement a Job Description Analyzer that parses and structures job requirements into a machine‐readable format\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nclass JobDescriptionAnalyzer:\\n    def __init__(self, job_description):\\n        self.job_description = job_description\\n        self.structured_data = {}\\n\\n    def parse_job_description(self):\\n        # Placeholder for parsing logic\\n        # This will be replaced with actual parsing using NLP techniques\\n        # and keyword extraction to identify key requirements, skills, etc.\\n        self.structured_data = {\\n            \\\"title\\\": self.extract_title(),\\n            \\\"summary\\\": self.extract_summary(),\\n            \\\"responsibilities\\\": self.extract_responsibilities(),\\n            \\\"qualifications\\\": self.extract_qualifications(),\\n            \\\"skills\\\": self.extract_skills(),\\n            \\\"experience\\\": self.extract_experience(),\\n            \\\"education\\\": self.extract_education()\\n        }\\n        return self.structured_data\\n\\n    def extract_title(self):\\n        # Placeholder for title extraction logic\\n        return \\\"Software Engineer\\\"  # Example\\n\\n    def extract_summary(self):\\n        # Placeholder for summary extraction logic\\n        return \\\"Seeking a skilled software engineer...\\\"  # Example\\n\\n    def extract_responsibilities(self):\\n         # Placeholder for responsibilities extraction logic\\n        return [\\\"Develop and maintain software\\\", \\\"Write clean code\\\"]  # Example\\n\\n    def extract_qualifications(self):\\n        # Placeholder for qualifications extraction logic\\n        return [\\\"Bachelor's degree in CS\\\", \\\"3+ years experience\\\"]  # Example\\n\\n    def extract_skills(self):\\n        # Placeholder for skills extraction logic\\n        return [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Java\\\", \\\"SQL\\\"]  # Example\\n\\n    def extract_experience(self):\\n        # Placeholder for experience extraction logic\\n        return \\\"3+ years of software development experience\\\" #Example\\n\\n    def extract_education(self):\\n        # Placeholder for education extraction logic\\n        return \\\"Bachelor's degree in Computer Science or related field\\\" #Example\\n\\n    def get_structured_data(self):\\n        return self.structured_data\\n\\n# Example usage (assuming job_description is a string containing the job description):\\n# analyzer = JobDescriptionAnalyzer(job_description)\\n# structured_job_data = analyzer.parse_job_description()\\n# print(structured_job_data)\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-27T16:53:01.158503\"\n}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 16:53:06,804", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nYou are a workflow planning agent.\\nYour task is to:\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n\\nReturn the output as a .txt file of all the steps taken to perform the tasks.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Build an Interview Module that generates technical questions dynamically based on structured JD and resume data\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Implement a Response Scorer that evaluates candidate answers against JD and resume criteria\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nDevelop a Resume Analyzer that extracts candidate skills, experience, and education into structured data\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport re\\nimport json\\n\\ndef analyze_resume(resume_text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Analyzes a resume to extract skills, experience, and education into a structured format.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        resume_text (str): The text content of the resume.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        dict: A dictionary containing extracted information, including:\\n            - skills (list): A list of skills extracted from the resume.\\n            - experience (list): A list of work experiences, each containing job title, company, dates, and description.\\n            - education (list): A list of educational qualifications, each containing institution, degree, and dates.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    skills = extract_skills(resume_text)\\n    experience = extract_experience(resume_text)\\n    education = extract_education(resume_text)\\n\\n    resume_data = {\\n        \\\"skills\\\": skills,\\n        \\\"experience\\\": experience,\\n        \\\"education\\\": education\\n    }\\n\\n    return resume_data\\n\\n\\ndef extract_skills(resume_text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Extracts skills from the resume text.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        resume_text (str): The text content of the resume.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of skills.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Define keywords and patterns for skill extraction (expand as needed)\\n    skill_keywords = [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Java\\\", \\\"C++\\\", \\\"JavaScript\\\", \\\"SQL\\\", \\\"AWS\\\", \\\"Azure\\\", \\\"GCP\\\", \\\"Machine Learning\\\", \\\"Data Science\\\", \\\"Project Management\\\"] #Example keywords\\n    skills = []\\n    for keyword in skill_keywords:\\n        if re.search(r'\\\\b' + re.escape(keyword) + r'\\\\b', resume_text, re.IGNORECASE):\\n            skills.append(keyword)\\n    return skills\\n\\n\\ndef extract_experience(resume_text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Extracts work experience from the resume text.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        resume_text (str): The text content of the resume.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of dictionaries, each representing a work experience.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Define patterns for experience extraction (improve regex as needed)\\n    experience_pattern = re.compile(\\n        r\\\"(?P<job_title>(?:[A-Za-z]+ ?)+)\\\\n\\\"  # Job Title\\n        r\\\"(?P<company>(?:[A-Za-z]+ ?)+)\\\\n\\\"  # Company Name\\n        r\\\"(?P<dates>(?:[A-Za-z]+ ?)+,?(?: ?[A-Za-z]+)? ?[-–] ?(?:[A-Za-z]+)?(?: ?[A-Za-z]+)?)\\\\n\\\"  # Dates\\n        r\\\"(?P<description>(?:.|\\\\n)*?)(?=\\\\n(?:[A-Za-z]+ ?)+\\\\n(?:[A-Za-z]+ ?)+\\\\n(?:[A-Za-z]+ ?)+,?(?: ?[A-Za-z]+)? ?[-–] ?(?:[A-Za-z]+)?(?: ?[A-Za-z]+)?|\\\\n(?:[A-Za-z]+ ?)+,?(?: ?[A-Za-z]+)? ?[-–] ?(?:[A-Za-z]+)?(?: ?[A-Za-z]+)?)\\\", # Description, stop before the next experience section,\\n        re.MULTILINE\\n    )\\n\\n    experiences = []\\n    for match in experience_pattern.finditer(resume_text):\\n        experience = {\\n            \\\"job_title\\\": match.group(\\\"job_title\\\").strip(),\\n            \\\"company\\\": match.group(\\\"company\\\").strip(),\\n            \\\"dates\\\": match.group(\\\"dates\\\").strip(),\\n            \\\"description\\\": match.group(\\\"description\\\").strip()\\n        }\\n        experiences.append(experience)\\n    return experiences\\n\\n\\ndef extract_education(resume_text):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Extracts education information from the resume text.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        resume_text (str): The text content of the resume.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        list: A list of dictionaries, each representing an educational qualification.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    # Define patterns for education extraction (improve regex as needed)\\n    education_pattern = re.compile(\\n        r\\\"(?P<institution>(?:[A-Za-z]+ ?)+)\\\\n\\\"\\n        r\\\"(?P<degree>(?:[A-Za-z]+ ?)+)\\\\n\\\"\\n        r\\\"(?P<dates>(?:[A-Za-z]+ ?)+,?(?: ?[A-Za-z]+)? ?[-–] ?(?:[A-Za-z]+)?(?: ?[A-Za-z]+)?(?: ?[A-Za-z]+)?)\\\\n\\\",\\n        re.MULTILINE\\n    )\\n\\n    education_list = []\\n    for match in education_pattern.finditer(resume_text):\\n        education = {\\n            \\\"institution\\\": match.group(\\\"institution\\\").strip(),\\n            \\\"degree\\\": match.group(\\\"degree\\\").strip(),\\n            \\\"dates\\\": match.group(\\\"dates\\\").strip()\\n        }\\n        education_list.append(education)\\n    return education_list\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage (Replace with actual resume text)\\n    resume_text = \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    John Doe\\n    john.doe@example.com\\n    123-456-7890\\n\\n    Summary\\n    Experienced software engineer with a passion for developing innovative solutions.\\n\\n    Skills\\n    Python, Java, C++, JavaScript, SQL, AWS\\n\\n    Experience\\n    Software Engineer\\n    Acme Corp\\n    2020 - Present\\n    - Developed and maintained web applications using Python and JavaScript.\\n    - Designed and implemented REST APIs.\\n    - Worked with AWS cloud services.\\n\\n    Data Scientist\\n    Beta Corp\\n    2018 - 2020\\n    - Developed machine learning models using Python.\\n    - Analyzed large datasets to identify trends and insights.\\n\\n    Education\\n    University of Example\\n    Bachelor of Science in Computer Science\\n    2014 - 2018\\n\\n    Stanford University\\n    Master of Science in Data Science\\n    2018 - 2020\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    resume_data = analyze_resume(resume_text)\\n\\n    # Output to JSON for structured format\\n    with open(\\\"resume_data.json\\\", \\\"w\\\") as f:\\n        json.dump(resume_data, f, indent=4)\\n\\n    print(\\\"Resume analysis complete.  Data saved to resume_data.json\\\")\\n```\\n\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-27T16:53:06.804280\"\n}"}
{"timestamp": "2026-05-27 16:53:07,610", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_2\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nYou are a workflow planning agent.\\nYour task is to:\\n-\\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n\\nReturn the output as a .txt file of all the steps taken to perform the tasks.\\n\\n\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nNo downstream objectives available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nCreate an Email Automation component to send templated messages at key workflow events\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport smtplib\\nfrom email.mime.multipart import MIMEMultipart\\nfrom email.mime.text import MIMEText\\n\\nclass EmailAutomation:\\n    def __init__(self, smtp_server, smtp_port, sender_email, sender_password):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the EmailAutomation component.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            smtp_server (str): The SMTP server address.\\n            smtp_port (int): The SMTP port number.\\n            sender_email (str): The sender's email address.\\n            sender_password (str): The sender's email password.  Consider using environment variables for security.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.smtp_server = smtp_server\\n        self.smtp_port = smtp_port\\n        self.sender_email = sender_email\\n        self.sender_password = sender_password\\n        self.server = None  # Initialize server attribute\\n\\n    def connect(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Connects to the SMTP server.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        try:\\n            self.server = smtplib.SMTP(self.smtp_server, self.smtp_port)\\n            self.server.starttls()  # Secure the connection\\n            self.server.login(self.sender_email, self.sender_password)\\n            print(\\\"Email server connection established.\\\")\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            print(f\\\"Error connecting to email server: {e}\\\")\\n            self.server = None # Ensure server is None if connection fails\\n\\n\\n    def disconnect(self):\\n         \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n         Disconnects to the SMTP server.\\n         \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n         if self.server:\\n            self.server.quit()\\n            print(\\\"Email server connection disconnected.\\\")\\n\\n    def send_email(self, recipient_email, subject, body, cc_email=None, bcc_email=None):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Sends an email.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            recipient_email (str): The recipient's email address.\\n            subject (str): The email subject.\\n            body (str): The email body (plain text or HTML).\\n            cc_email (str, optional): CC recipient email address. Defaults to None.\\n            bcc_email (str, optional): BCC recipient email address. Defaults to None.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            bool: True if the email was sent successfully, False otherwise.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if not self.server:\\n            print(\\\"Not connected to email server.  Call connect() first.\\\")\\n            return False\\n\\n        msg = MIMEMultipart()\\n        msg['From'] = self.sender_email\\n        msg['To'] = recipient_email\\n        msg['Subject'] = subject\\n\\n        if cc_email:\\n            msg['Cc'] = cc_email\\n        if bcc_email:\\n            msg['Bcc'] = bcc_email\\n\\n        msg.attach(MIMEText(body, 'plain'))  # Or 'html' for HTML emails\\n\\n        try:\\n            recipients = [recipient_email]\\n            if cc_email:\\n                recipients.append(cc_email)\\n            if bcc_email:\\n                recipients.append(bcc_email)\\n\\n            self.server.sendmail(self.sender_email, recipients, msg.as_string())\\n            print(f\\\"Email sent successfully to {recipient_email}\\\")\\n            return True\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            print(f\\\"Error sending email: {e}\\\")\\n            return False\\n\\n    def create_template(self, template_name, subject_template, body_template):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Stores email templates for future use.\\n        (This implementation just stores them in memory, consider a file or database)\\n\\n        Args:\\n            template_name (str): The name of the template.\\n            subject_template (str): The template for the subject.\\n            body_template (str): The template for the body.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if not hasattr(self, 'templates'):\\n            self.templates = {}  # Initialize the templates dictionary if it doesn't exist\\n\\n        self.templates[template_name] = {'subject': subject_template, 'body': body_template}\\n        print(f\\\"Template '{template_name}' created and stored.\\\")\\n\\n    def send_templated_email(self, recipient_email, template_name, template_data, cc_email=None, bcc_email=None):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Sends an email using a stored template.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            recipient_email (str): The recipient's email address.\\n            template_name (str): The name of the template to use.\\n            template_data (dict): A dictionary of data to insert into the template.\\n            cc_email (str, optional): CC recipient email address. Defaults to None.\\n            bcc_email (str, optional): BCC recipient email address. Defaults to None.\\n\\n        Returns:\\n            bool: True if the email was sent successfully, False otherwise.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if not hasattr(self, 'templates') or template_name not in self.templates:\\n            print(f\\\"Template '{template_name}' not found.\\\")\\n            return False\\n\\n        template = self.templates[template_name]\\n        subject = template['subject'].format(**template_data)\\n        body = template['body'].format(**template_data)\\n        return self.send_email(recipient_email, subject, body, cc_email, bcc_email)\\n\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == '__main__':\\n    # Example Usage (Replace with your actual credentials and server details)\\n    smtp_server = 'your_smtp_server.com'  # Replace with your SMTP server address\\n    smtp_port = 587  # Replace with your SMTP port number (e.g., 587 for TLS)\\n    sender_email = 'your_email@example.com'  # Replace with your email address\\n    sender_password = 'your_email_password'  # Replace with your email password (use environment variables in production!)\\n\\n    email_automation = EmailAutomation(smtp_server, smtp_port, sender_email, sender_password)\\n\\n    # Connect to the email server\\n    email_automation.connect()\\n\\n    # 1. Sending a Simple Email\\n    recipient_email = 'recipient@example.com'\\n    subject = 'Test Email'\\n    body = 'This is a test email sent using the EmailAutomation component.'\\n    email_automation.send_email(recipient_email, subject, body)\\n\\n    # 2. Creating and Using a Template\\n    email_automation.create_template(\\n        'interview_invitation',\\n        'Interview Invitation for {candidate_name}',\\n        'Dear {candidate_name},\\\\n\\\\nYou are invited to an interview on {date} at {time}.\\\\n\\\\nSincerely,\\\\nThe Hiring Team'\\n    )\\n\\n    template_data = {'candidate_name': 'John Doe', 'date': '2023-12-25', 'time': '10:00 AM'}\\n    email_automation.send_templated_email(recipient_email, 'interview_invitation', template_data)\\n\\n\\n    # 3. Sending Email With CC and BCC\\n    email_automation.send_email(\\n        recipient_email='primary_recipient@example.com',\\n        subject='Important Announcement',\\n        body='This is an important announcement email.',\\n        cc_email='cc_recipient@example.com',\\n        bcc_email='bcc_recipient@example.com'\\n    )\\n    # Disconnect from the email server\\n    email_automation.disconnect()\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-27T16:53:07.610018\"\n}"}
