ntained microservices at TechCorp\\n  - Familiar with AWS, Docker, Kubernetes\\nSkills Matched:\\n  - Python/Django: Expert\\n  - API Design: Strong\\n  - Databases: PostgreSQL, MongoDB\\n  - CI/CD: Jenkins, GitLab CI\\n\\n3. Interview Questions Asked\\n----------------------------\\nQ1: Explain how you would design a scalable REST API for a high-traffic service.\\nQ2: Describe your approach to database indexing and query optimization.\\nQ3: How do you implement automated testing and CI/CD pipelines?\\nQ4: What monitoring tools have you used in production environments?\\n\\n4. Candidate Responses\\n----------------------\\nQ1 Response:\\n  \\\"I would start with defining resources and endpoints, use load balancers,\\n  containerize services, implement rate limiting and caching (Redis), and\\n  use auto-scaling groups on AWS...\\\"\\n\\nQ2 Response:\\n  \\\"I analyze query patterns, add composite indexes on high-filter columns,\\n  use EXPLAIN plans to detect bottlenecks, and archive old data to reduce table size...\\\"\\n\\nQ3 Response:\\n  \\\"I write unit and integration tests with pytest, configure coverage thresholds,\\n  set up Jenkins pipelines to run tests on every commit, and deploy to staging on success...\\\"\\n\\nQ4 Response:\\n  \\\"I’ve used Prometheus for metrics collection, Grafana for dashboards,\\n  and ELK stack for log aggregation and analysis...\\\"\\n\\n5. Scoring Breakdown\\n--------------------\\nCriteria              Weight  Score (out of 10)  Weighted Score\\n--------------------------------------------------------------\\nTechnical Knowledge     40%          8                 3.2\\nProblem Solving         30%          7                 2.1\\nBest Practices          20%          9                 1.8\\nCommunication           10%          8                 0.8\\n--------------------------------------------------------------\\nTotal Weighted Score: 7.9 / 10\\n\\n6. Overall Evaluation\\n---------------------\\nStrengths:\\n  - Deep backend expertise in Python/Django\\n  - Strong understanding of API design and scaling\\n  - Familiar with modern CI/CD and monitoring tools\\n\\nAreas for Improvement:\\n  - Could elaborate more on database sharding strategies\\n  - Limited exposure to serverless architectures\\n\\nRecommendation:\\n  Hire for Senior Backend Engineer role with a starting focus on mentoring and leading service-scaling projects.\\n\\n===============================\\nReport generated on: 2024-06-05\\nPrepared by: Automated Report Generator v1.0\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## VERSION 1\\n```txt\\n1. Analyze the job description using JobDescriptionAnalyzer to extract key information such as skills, experience, and education requirements.\\n2. Analyze the candidate's resume using the resume analysis module to extract skills, experience, and education details.\\n3. Use the Interview Module to generate technical interview questions based on the analyzed job description and resume data.\\n4. Send the generated interview questions to the candidate via Email Automation.\\n5. Conduct the technical interview with the candidate.\\n6. Receive the candidate's responses to the interview questions.\\n7. Score each candidate response using the Response Scorer, considering the job description, resume data, and predefined weights for different criteria.\\n8. Store the scores and feedback for each question.\\n9. Generate a final evaluation report including:\\n    a. Summary of the job description analysis.\\n    b. Summary of the resume analysis.\\n    c. List of interview questions asked.\\n    d. Candidate's responses to each question.\\n    e. Scores for each response.\\n    f. Overall score and evaluation of the candidate.\\n10. Send the final evaluation report to the hiring manager via Email Automation.\\n\\n===============================\\nCandidate Evaluation Report\\n===============================\\n\\n1. Job Description Analysis\\n----------------------------\\nPosition Title: [Position Title]\\nKey Skills Required:\\n  - [Skill 1], [Skill 2], [Skill 3]\\nExperience & Education:\\n  - [Years] + years [Experience Type]\\n  - [Degree] in [Field] or equivalent\\n\\n2. Resume Analysis\\n------------------\\nCandidate Name: [Candidate Name]\\nSummary:\\n  - [Candidate Summary]\\nSkills Matched:\\n  - [Skill 1]: [Proficiency Level]\\n  - [Skill 2]: [Proficiency Level]\\n\\n3. Interview Questions Asked\\n----------------------------\\nQ1: [Question 1]\\nQ2: [Question 2]\\nQ3: [Question 3]\\nQ4: [Question 4]\\n\\n4. Candidate Responses\\n----------------------\\nQ1 Response:\\n  [Candidate Response to Q1]\\n\\nQ2 Response:\\n  [Candidate Response to Q2]\\n\\nQ3 Response:\\n  [Candidate Response to Q3]\\n\\nQ4 Response:\\n  [Candidate Response to Q4]\\n\\n5. Scoring Breakdown\\n--------------------\\nCriteria              Weight  Score (out of 10)  Weighted Score\\n--------------------------------------------------------------\\nTechnical Knowledge     40%          [Score 1]          [Weighted Score 1]\\nProblem Solving         30%          [Score 2]          [Weighted Score 2]\\nBest Practices          20%          [Score 3]          [Weighted Score 3]\\nCommunication           10%          [Score 4]          [Weighted Score 4]\\n--------------------------------------------------------------\\nTotal Weighted Score: [Total Weighted Score] / 10\\n\\n6. Overall Evaluation\\n---------------------\\nStrengths:\\n  - [Strength 1]\\n  - [Strength 2]\\n\\nAreas for Improvement:\\n  - [Area for Improvement 1]\\n  - [Area for Improvement 2]\\n\\nRecommendation:\\n  [Recommendation]\\n\\n===============================\\nReport generated on: [Date]\\nPrepared by: Automated Report Generator v1.0\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 1\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The output mixes the workflow plan and a template but does not provide a single plain‐text “.txt”